message.content:
A skyscraper is a tall, multi-story building usually found in urban areas.
They are characterized by their height and size, often towering over other buildings around them.
Most skyscrapers feature a steel frame construction with glass windows and a concrete or metal exterior.
Their architectural design can vary greatly, but they tend to have a narrow and elongated shape.
Typically used as office spaces or residential units, skyscrapers offer unique views of the surrounding cityscape.
They have become iconic symbols of modern cities and are often featured prominently in their skylines.
Skyscrapers have played a significant role in urban development and have revolutionized the way we use urban spaces.
